Description: Triple-reeded handle sherd of North Ionian pottery vessel, probably an oinochoe, with part of rim join; white slip; exterior: black band on either side of handle extending to break on inside; short horizontals on each reed; at top, pair of horizontal bands below palmette and tendril motif.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.101)
